You will be given 9 chances to interact with functions to gather relevant information. An example answer would look like follows.

Title: Diagnosis of test `testGenerateURLFragment`
Details: The test `testGenerateURLFragment` checks whether HTML entities such as `"` are correctly escaped to their corresponding character by the `StandardToolTipTagFragmentGenerator.generateToolTipFragment` method. However, the test failure indicates that this is not the case. Following the execution path, we find that `StandardToolTipTagFragmentGenerator.generateToolTipFragment` is not escaping any HTML code; instead, it is using its input `toolTipText` as is. Consequently, un-escaped strings are being returned, which leads to the error demonstrated by the test.

After providing this diagnosis, you will be prompted to suggest which methods would be the best locations to be fixed. The failing test `com.google.javascript.jscomp.NodeUtilTest.testLocalValue1()` is testing the method `NodeUtil.evaluatesToLocalValue(Node value, Predicate<Node> locals)` in the `NodeUtil` class. The test encountered an `IllegalStateException` with the message "Unexpected expression nodeDELPROP 1", which indicates that there was an unexpected expression node encountered during the evaluation of whether a value is local.

The `evaluatesToLocalValue` method in the `NodeUtil` class checks whether a given node value evaluates to a local value based on certain conditions. One key condition is whether the node value is considered immutable or not. The `isImmutableValue` method in the `NodeUtil` class is used to determine if a node is immutable by checking its type.

In this case, the error occurred when handling the node type `DELPROP`. The `DELPROP` node type is not explicitly handled in the `evaluatesToLocalValue` method, which results in the `IllegalStateException` being thrown when encountering this unexpected node type.

To fix this issue, the `evaluatesToLocalValue` method needs to be updated to handle the `DELPROP` node type or address why this node type is reaching this point unexpectedly.

Suggested fix:
```java
com.google.javascript.jscomp.NodeUtil.evaluatesToLocalValue(com.google.javascript.rhino.Node, com.google.common.base.Predicate<com.google.javascript.rhino.Node>)
com.google.google.javascript.jscomp.NodeUtil.isImmutableValue(com.google.google.javascript.rhino.Node)
```

Based on the available information, provide the signatures of the most likely culprit methods for the bug. Your answer will be processed automatically, so make sure to only answer with the accurate signatures of all likely culprits (in `ClassName.MethodName(ArgType1, ArgType2, ...)` format), without commentary (one per line).
